        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 6:00PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 600 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hawkinsville, or 13 miles north of Eufaula, moving northeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hawkinsville, Russell County Sports Complex, Spring Hill, Seale,
Lakepoint Resort State Park, Uchee Creek, Fort Mitchell, Fort
Mitchell Activity Center, Parkmanville, and Twin Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
